        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-19T14:38:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think I did something like this at PS4.  We obtain the updated copies of the repos, use those to create (but not yet insert) new jobs and freshen the caches.  Then we \"commit\" the updates to the repos, and insert the new jobs afterward.  That ensures that the repos always have the commits for the new jobs, and the caches always contain entries for the new commits.",
